Value: Kula Gold Limited identifies and explores for metals in Western Australia. The company primarily explores for gold, nickel, and copper deposits, as well as platinum group elements. It holds 100% interests in the Airfield gold project covering an area of approximately 120 km2 located to the east of the town of Marvel Loch, Western Australia; the Rankin Dome gold and nickel project situated to west and north west of the town of Southern Cross, Western Australia; the Brunswick PGE-AU project covering an area of 240 km2 located in the southwest region of western Australia; and the Lake Rebecca gold project covering an area of approximately 150 km2 situated in Kalgoorlie, Western Australia. The company was incorporated in 2007 and is based in Perth, Australia.
